{"artifact_links": ["https://simonwillison.net/2026/Jun/6/micropython-in-a-sandbox"], "author_or_org": null, "canonical_url": "https://simonwillison.net/2026/Jun/6/micropython-in-a-sandbox", "collection_method": "rss_atom", "confidence": "high", "content_hash": "219da0da3d2736d1", "dedup_key": "rss-guid:simonwillison-blog:https://simonwillison.net/2026/Jun/6/micropython-in-a-sandbox/#atom-everything", "event_id": "event_481a034f878bd679", "evidence_type": "supported_fact", "excerpt": "<p>I've been experimenting with different approaches to running code in a sandbox for several years now, but my latest attempt feels like it might finally have all of the characteristics I've been looking for. I've released it as an alpha package called <a href=\"https://github.com/simonw/micropython-wasm\">micropython-wasm</a>, and I'm using it for a code execution sandbox plugin for <a href=\"https://github.com/datasette/datasette-agent\">Datasette Agent</a> called <a href=\"https://github.com/datasette/datasette-agent-micropython\">datasette-agent-micropython</a>.</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Jun/6/micropython-in-a-sandbox/#why-do-i-want-a-sandbox-\">Why do I want a sandbox?</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Jun/6/micropython-in-a-sandbox/#what-i-want-from-a-sandbox\">What I want from a sandbox</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Jun/6/micropython-in-a-sandbox/#webassembly-looks-really-promising-here\">WebAssembly looks really promising here</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Jun/6/micropython-in-a-sandbox/#micropython-in-webassembly\">MicroPython in WebAssembly</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://simonwilli", "identifiers": {}, "inferred_entities": [], "item_type": "rss_atom_item", "novelty_score": 0.0, "published_at": "2026-06-06T03:53:34+00:00", "ranking_explanation": "", "raw_metadata": {}, "relevance_score": 0.0, "retrieved_at": "2026-06-06T22:26:28Z", "source_id": "simonwillison-blog", "source_name": "Simon Willison's Weblog", "source_native_id": "https://simonwillison.net/2026/Jun/6/micropython-in-a-sandbox/#atom-everything", "source_policy": "public_official", "source_type": "primary_artifact", "summary_hint": "<p>I've been experimenting with different approaches to running code in a sandbox for several years now, but my latest attempt feels like it might finally have all of the characteristics I've been looking for. I've released it as an alpha package called <a href=\"https://github.com/simonw/micropython-wasm\">micropython-wasm</a>, and I'm using it for a code execution sandbox plugin for <a href=\"https://github.com/datasette/datasette-agent\">Datasette Agent</a> called <a href=\"https://github.com/datasette/datasette-agent-micropython\">datasette-agent-micropython</a>.</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Jun/6/micropython-in-a-sandbox/#why-do-i-want-a-sandbox-\">Why do I want a sandbox?</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Jun/6/micropython-in-a-sandbox/#what-i-want-from-a-sandbox\">What I want from a sandbox</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Jun/6/micropython-in-a-sandbox/#webassembly-looks-really-promising-here\">WebAssembly looks really promising here</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Jun/6/micropython-in-a-sandbox/#micropython-in-webassembly\">MicroPython in WebAssembly</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://simonwilli", "title": "Running Python code in a sandbox with MicroPython and WASM", "topics": ["topic_running-python-code-sandbox-with"], "updated_at": null}
